{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λεπ-ίς</b>, ίδος, ἡ, <br /> (λέπω) <b>epithelial debris</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 4.81 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>layer</b> of the skull, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PMed.” in “Arch.Papyrus” 4.270\">Refs</a>]; ᾠοῦ λ. egg-<b>shell</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 198 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>cup</b> of a filbert, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 6.22 (from Zonas), 102 (1st c.AD: Philippus Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>coat</b> of an onion, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Hist.Conscr.” 26. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> collectively, <b>scales</b> of fish, λεπίδος σιδηρέης ὄψιν ἰχθυοειδέος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.61; ὃ ἐν ὄρνιθι πτερόν, τοῦτο ἐν ἰχθύϊ ἐστὶ λ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 486b21; opposed to φολίς, [prev. work] 490b23, 517b5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of serpents, variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Theriaca” 154, compare 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 82. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of other things, λ. χαλκοῦ <b>flakes</b> that fly from copper in hammering, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 5.78, 79: _absolutely_, λεπίς 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “γυναικεῖα” 1.63. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>plate</b> of metal, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 69.50, 2nd-1st c.BC(?): Hero Mechanicus “Automatopoetica” 12.2, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.91, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Phocion” 18; collectively, λ. σιδηρᾶ “BGU” 544.8 (2nd c.AD) \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; of gold and silver, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.27.10; λ. ἀργυρᾶ “PMag.Par.” 1.258. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> λ. πρίονος <b>blade</b> of a saw, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Heliodorus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 47.14.5. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> λεπίδες (i.e. χιόνος) snow-<b>flakes</b>, conjecture in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.14.13, “CP” 5.12.11. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3013","accentedUnicode":"λεπίς","shortDef":"scale, flake","mediumDef":"scale, flake <br /><b>a scale, shell, rind, crust, incrustation, flake</b> <ref='Act.9.18'>Acts 9:18</ref>*","stepGloss":"scale","stepTransliteration":"lepis","count":1,"_es_Definition":"lámina, escama (de pez)","_zh_tw_Definition":"鱗片 (徒 9:18)","_zh_Definition":"鳞片 (徒 9:18)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"cái vảy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"鱗","_es_Gloss":"escama","_zh_Gloss":"鳞"}]}